Section 1:
1 L.D. 20
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 33, L.D. 20, “An Act Regarding the First
10 Judicial District and the District Court Locations in the Judicial Divisions of Androscoggin
11 and Western Aroostook”
12 Amend the bill by inserting after section 4 the following:
13 'Sec. 5. Reallocation of Western Aroostook and Eastern Aroostook judicial
14 divisions. Notwithstanding the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 4, section 153, subsections
15 3 and 4, for the convenience of the public, the Chief Judge of the District Court may, by
16 order, which may from time to time be amended or repealed, reallocate any municipality
17 or unorganized territory between the Western Aroostook and Eastern Aroostook judicial
18 divisions. Copies of the order must be posted on the judicial branch's publicly accessible
19 website.
20 Sec. 6. Report. By January 15, 2026, the Chief Judge of the District Court shall
21 submit a report to the Joint Standing Committee on Judiciary with any recommendations
22 for redrawing the geographic boundaries between any of the judicial divisions set forth in
23 the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 4, section 153. The committee may report out legislation
24 based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
25 Sec. 7. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
26 allocations are made.
27 JUDICIAL DEPARTMENT
28 Courts - Supreme, Superior and District 0063
29 Initiative: Provides ongoing deappropriations due to the closure of the district court in
30 Madawaska.
31 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
32 Personal Services ($5,416) ($6,500)
33 All Other ($38,640) ($46,368)
34 __________ __________
35 GENERAL FUND TOTAL ($44,056) ($52,868)
Page 1 - 132LR0279(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 33, L.D. 20
11 '
2 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
3 number to read consecutively.
4 SUMMARY
55 This amendment authorizes the Chief Judge of the District Court to issue an order,
66 which must be made publicly available, reallocating any municipality or unorganized
77 territory between the Western Aroostook and Eastern Aroostook judicial divisions of the
88 State. The amendment also directs the Chief Judge to submit a report by January 15, 2026
99 to the Joint Standing Committee on Judiciary with recommendations for redrawing the
1100 geographic boundaries between any of the judicial divisions in the State and authorizes the
1111 committee to report out legislation based on the report.
12 The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section recognizing the
13 cost savings attendant to closure of the Madawaska District Court.
1144 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1155 (See attached)
